{#- BRIDGE → prose -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-controller-bridge">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Controller and CFO</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Accurate books are what make strategy possible.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The controller and the CFO are different jobs that depend on each other. A CFO building a forecast, a board package, or a fundraising model on books no one has verified is building on sand &mdash; which is exactly why a fractional CFO&rsquo;s first move on a new engagement is to assess the accounting underneath. A controller is the role that removes that problem: the numbers are right, on time, every month, before the CFO ever opens them.</p>
      <p>Many businesses run both &mdash; controller for accuracy and oversight, <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">fractional CFO</a> for strategy &mdash; and where TechBrot delivers the bookkeeping, controller, and CFO layers together, the whole finance stack runs as one system instead of three vendors handing off to each other. As automation handles the routine recording, the controller&rsquo;s accountability and the CFO&rsquo;s judgment are where the value concentrates. <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">Explore fractional CFO <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- FAQ-EXTRA → trailing baseline prose block (supervise anchor preserved) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-controller-faq-extra">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="prose" id="acct-controller-supervise">
      <p><strong>Can the controller supervise our existing bookkeeper?</strong> Yes. Controller services can supervise an internal bookkeeper, a third-party bookkeeping vendor, TechBrot&rsquo;s own bookkeeping team, or a combination. The controller&rsquo;s job is oversight and accountability &mdash; reviewing and directing the recording work, not necessarily doing all of it. Where TechBrot also provides the bookkeeping underneath, the controller is supervising a function we operate end to end, which removes the handoff friction entirely.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

